ized form of German <b>Perschall</b>, a variant of <b>Parschall</b> (see   Parshall  ); alternatively, a variant of <b>Perschel</b>, from a pet form of <b>Persch</b>, a short form of   Berthold   or   Peter   in the border area with Czechia."],"variants":[{"name":"Parshall","meanings":["Americanized form of South German <b>Parschall</b>, a variant of <b>Parschalk</b>, a status name for a freeholder (a freeman with few service obligations), from Middle High German <i>bar</i> ‘naked’, ‘free from, apparent’ + <i>schalk</i> ‘servant, man’. See   Pershall  .","English: variant of   Pearsall  ."]}]},{"name":"Eleanor","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."],"variants":[{"name":"Ellenor","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Eleanor  , the result of blending with   Ellen ."]},{"name":"Elenor","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."]},{"name":"Elinor","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Eleanor ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Eleanor de Pershale was born about 1186, in France, her father, Stephen De Pershale, was 47 and her mother, Miss Barrett, was 46. She had at least 1 son with John Swynnerton."},"et":{"about 1186–":"umbes 1186–Surnud","1186–Female":"1186–Surnud","1208–1254":"1208–1254","1215–1250":"1215–1250","1140–Male":"1140–Surnud","1142–Female":"1142–Surnud","1215":"1215","1254":"1254","1142":"1142","1186":"1186","1140":"1140","1250":"1250","1208":"1208","about 1186":"umbes 1186","of, Swynerton, France":"Prantsusmaa","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1186–":"noin 1186–Kuollut","1186–Female":"1186–Kuollut","1208–1254":"1208–1254","1215–1250":"1215–1250","1140–Male":"1140–Kuollut","1142–Female":"1142–Kuollut","1215":"1215","1254":"1254","1142":"1142","1186":"1186","1140":"1140","1250":"1250","1208":"1208","about 1186":"noin 1186","of, Swynerton, France":"Ranska","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1186–":"environ 1186–Décédée","1186–Female":"1186–Décédée","1208–1254":"1208–1254","1215–1250":"1215–1250","1140–Male":"1140–Décédé","1142–Female":"1142–Décédée","1215":"1215","1254":"1254","1142":"1142","1186":"1186","1140":"1140","1250":"1250","1208":"1208","about 1186":"environ 1186","of, Swynerton, France":"France","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Eleanor de Pershale est née environ 1186, à France, son père, Stephen De Pershale, avait 47 ans et sa mère, Miss Barrett, avait 46 ans. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec John Swynnerton."},"de":{"about 1186–":"um 1186–Verstorben","1186–Female":"1186–Verstorben","1208–1254":"1208–1254","1215–1250":"1215–1250","1140–Male":"1140–Verstorben","1142–Female":"1142–Verstorben","1215":"1215","1254":"1254","1142":"1142","1186":"1186","1140":"1140","1250":"1250","1208":"1208","about 1186":"um 1186","of, Swynerton, France":"Frankreich","England":"England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Als Eleanor de Pershale um 1186 in Frankreich geboren wurde, war ihr Vater 